# Frontend Architecture

## Component Scope вЂ” Where to Place Components

Before creating a component, determine its scope:

- **`src/components/common/`** вЂ” Reusable UI components with no feature-specific logic. Can be used anywhere in the app (e.g. `MoneyInput`, `DatePicker`, `Avatar`). If a component could reasonably be used in more than one feature, it belongs here.
- **`src/components/<FeatureName>/components/`** вЂ” Sub-components owned by a single feature. They depend on feature-specific types, context, or logic and should never be imported outside that feature.

When in doubt, ask: *"Could another feature use this without modification?"* If yes в†’ `common/`. If no в†’ keep it inside the feature.

