## Utils

- Each util lives in its own folder: `utils/utilName/index.ts`
- Any hardcoded value that could change (locale strings, regex patterns, magic strings, numeric thresholds, API paths, etc.) must live in the nearest `constants/index.ts` file, never inlined in the implementation
- Utils must be pure functions with no side effects

## File Naming вЂ” STRICT

- All files are named `index.tsx` (components) or `index.ts` (non-React)
- Never use the feature name as the filename: `BikeCard.tsx` вќЊ в†’ `BikeCard/index.tsx` вњ…
- Imports use the folder path: `from '@/utils/debounce'` вњ…, never `from '@/utils/debounce/index'` вќЊ

## Types

- Types prefixed with `T` в†’ `TBikeCard`, `TUserData`
- Interfaces prefixed with `I` в†’ `IBikeCardProps`, `IApiResponse`
- No `any`
- No `@ts-ignore` / `@ts-expect-error` without written justification
- Functions must have explicit return types
- **All** type definitions must live in a `types/index.ts` file alongside the implementation вЂ” defining types inside the implementation file is forbidden

## Components

- One component = one responsibility (SRP)
- **Each file must export exactly one component. Defining more than one component in the same file is forbidden** вЂ” extract any secondary component to its own folder under `components/`
- **Render functions (functions that return JSX) are components and must be extracted** вЂ” a function like `const renderSkeleton = () => <Box>...</Box>` defined inside a component file is forbidden; extract it as a proper component in its own `components/ComponentName/index.tsx`
- **JSX assigned to a variable inside a component is also a component** вЂ” a pattern like `const banner = <Box>...</Box>` used as a UI section must be extracted to its own component file, not defined inline
- Keep components small and reusable вЂ” if a component can be split into sub-components, it should be
- **All state and event handlers must live in a custom hook** вЂ” the component file must only contain the JSX return and the hook invocation. No `useState`, `useEffect`, `useCallback`, `useRef`, or handler functions defined directly in the component body
- Helper functions must never be defined inside a component file вЂ” every helper belongs in its own `utils/helperName/index.ts` file and imported explicitly
- Props destructured at the top of the component
- No complex logic in JSX вЂ” extract to functions or variables
- No over-engineering: only what the task requires
- No unrequested features
- No refactoring of code unrelated to the task

## Documentation

- All utility functions must have JSDoc with `@param`, `@returns` and a description
- All custom hooks must have JSDoc
- **No inline comments of any kind inside component or hook files** вЂ” the code must be self-explanatory. The only exception is JSDoc blocks on utils and hooks

## Code Quality

- No `console.log` or `console.*` вЂ” use the project logger (`src/logger/`)
- No unused imports
- No commented-out code (dead code)
- No `_` prefix variables as compatibility hacks
- No magic numbers, hardcoded strings, or inline configuration вЂ” use named constants in the nearest `constants/index.ts`

## Styles

- No inline styles without justification
- Mobile-first design
- Accessibility: ARIA labels and semantic HTML

## Security & Performance

- Validate only at system boundaries (user input, external APIs)
- No XSS, SQL injection, or command injection vulnerabilities
- No sensitive data exposed on the client
- Cleanup side-effect hooks to prevent memory leaks
- Use `useMemo`/`useCallback` only when a real re-render problem has been measured
